annotation.TEXT: Find out next time! To be continued...
MOOOOOONNNNN!!!!!!!

1 vote for the light switch in my bathroom, 1 vote to try one switch first and then the other if there are any significant changes between them, 1 vote for both switches (not possible, unfortunately), 1 vote to flip a coin to decide the switch, 2 votes for neither switch, 4 votes for the yellow switch, and 7 votes for the green switch! I guess green wins!
Whoa! That was super lucky!
Well, I hit green, so... Gimme! Gimme! Gimme!
Oh, but I thought I saw something else up above, so I'm going to go check that out.
Alright, I've reset the game again, and now I'm going to try getting the normal exit first this time.
Now, this place appears to be unchanged, so while I'm looting the area, I'll announce the voting results of which switch I should hit here...
Well, I wouldn't mind if the farmers destroyed the munchers...
Hello, this is SomeGuy712x, and welcome to...
Oooohhhh! It's part of the background! Of course! Hey, cavern, stop playing games with my mind... game... mind... game... mind... game...

The floating coin that could cause an invisible solid block glitch over here has been removed. Though, that coin also served as a hint for these hidden blocks, so I would've just moved it up one space instead of removing it.
Now, what's so great about this castle?
Ooh, "The Switch's Reward"! Finally, a payoff for all of my hard work!
That opens the 2-Way Switch as usual, but if I were to get the normal exit now, would that still cause the switch palace to collapse early on me?
And there's the last Yoshi coin. Alright, so let's put the key in the keyhole here...
I wonder if I'm supposed to be able to reach that goal sphere, maybe with the P-switch... Well, let me look around some more first.
Well, the P-switch door led to this goal.
No, I missed a coin. My OCD! Okay, so down here, we now have a ? block that holds the key, which means this shell was important!
Oh, man. I hope I don't have to "Yakety Sax" this part... (I still remember a climbing segment like this from another hack from long ago!)
Ah, but things are different in "Welcome!". First of all, there are more Yoshi coins.
Looks like green allowed me to run up here and get some coins...
Well, bye, Yoshi!
Well, I may as well scout ahead before resetting the level.
Wait, I can't even interact with it...
MOOOONNN!!! I must have it! But, how do I reach it? Maybe with the P-switch?
May as well try out that other door while I'm here.
Ow.
And, it's a reset door, that also reset the music for some reason.
Bye, Yoshi! And the moon is mine!!! (Insert evil-sounding Laharl-like laugh here.)
So, we have a power up and a door...
Hi, Yoshi! I bet most (if not all) of you can guess what I'm going to do with this horse!
Ehh, 29 from the ground is okay, I guess, and it's plenty enough to trigger a bonus game!
Midpoint already? That was fast. (And no puzzle at all? Then what's the reset door for?)
I don't see the point of this vine.
And, we're done with this level!
...DODODO's "Mini Levels"! Wait, I already did this introduction, right? Well, I received an updated version from helpful123456789, so let's see what's changed.
Maybe I'll need this ice block for something... That would explain the reset door.
Tricks, like with that tiny slope in the middle of the ground right there?
Alright, time for brand new content, starting with Muncher Paradise! Oh, that sounds lovely...
Hi, Yoshi! And I take it I can jump over the goal from here?
D'oh, I missed...
Water level music?
Aw, man... I'm not seeing anything resembling a way to the moon with that P-switch activation...

And now for the secret exit. I'm not entirely in favor of requiring the shell for the key block, though. If you don't bring the shell, or you lose/destroy it, you'll be trapped over in the keyhole area.
Well, I see a P-switch door up there, but no obvious path to the moon...
That opened up a great castle of some sort, but I'm not done with this cavern yet! I want that moon!
And up next, we have a cavern that is on the mischievious side. (Shouldn't that be spelled "Mischievous", without the "i" right before the "ous"?)
Pointless block factory FTW!
I'm not licked yet, though! I still have an idea on how to reach that moon! First let's revisit a previous level...
Oh, yeah! Jackpot!
Maybe you should include a reset door or pipe over here, just in case of such an occurrence.
And apparently, it's a reset door for some reason. I take it there's gonna be a "screw-uppable" puzzle in this level? Still, I can use this opportunity to stock up on flowers. Thanks!
Wait, what? I have to ditch Yoshi? What kind of reward is that?
Ah, so if I get the normal exit first, the switch palace won't be preflattened when I get the secret exit. Still, I'm going to do the switch palace now.
Well, the intro is no different, so let's speed through that.
The goal already?!?! But I just hit midpoint!
Well, there's a goal sphere, but... Yeah. I kind of expected that.
And so the green switch is pressed. However, I will consider backing up and trying out the yellow switch if there are any major differences between them in the near future.
Yoshi's Grove is unchanged...
Huh, it contains a shell for some reason. Well, it must be important, so I'll hang on to it.
Also, there's this ? block, which wasn't here before.
Oh, boy! That's a lot of bullet cannons!

So, green let me reach a moon, but forced me to ditch Yoshi, while yellow looked like it would just be worth a mushroom and a covered gap. Well, I would say that green is far better, since I can easily reclaim Yoshi in the previous level if needed.
Well, that's obviously not what the ice block should be used for... Whoa! Got lucky there!
Still nothing in that dead end.
MOOOOOOONNNNNN!!!!!!!!!

Yeah, unfortunately, it still collapses early. I have no idea what's causing it to do that, and helpful123456789 told me he triple-checked the events, and still can't figure it out. Any ideas what the problem is?
